{
  "local_port": 45178,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are things you realized only in your senior year of college?",
  "response": "The senior year of college is often a time of reflection, growth, and realization as students prepare to transition into the next phase of their lives. Here are some common insights people often realize during their senior year:\n\n### 1. **Time Moves Faster Than You Think**\n   - The realization that four years have flown by hits hard. Many seniors wish they had taken more advantage of opportunities earlier in their college career.\n\n### 2. **Networking Matters More Than You Thought**\n   - Building relationships with professors, peers, and professionals becomes crucial as you prepare for life after college. Many seniors realize the importance of maintaining connections.\n\n### 3. **Grades Aren\u2019t Everything**\n   - While academics are important, seniors often realize that experiences, internships, and personal growth matter just as much (if not more) than a perfect GPA.\n\n### 4. **You\u2019ll Miss the College Lifestyle**\n   - The freedom, friendships, and late-night study sessions become cherished memories. Many seniors realize they\u2019ll miss the simplicity of college life once it\u2019s over.\n\n### 5. **Adulting is Harder Than It Looks**\n   - The realities of budgeting, job searching, and navigating the \u201creal world\u201d start to hit home. Seniors often feel a mix of excitement and anxiety about what\u2019s next.\n\n### 6. **You\u2019ve Changed More Than You Realized**\n   - Reflecting on who you were as a freshman versus who you are now can be eye-opening. College shapes your identity in ways you may not have expected.\n\n### 7. **It\u2019s Okay Not to Have It All Figured Out**\n   - Many seniors feel pressure to have their careers and lives planned out, but they often realize it\u2019s okay to take things one step at a time.\n\n### 8. **The Importance of Self-Care**\n   - Balancing academics, social life, and mental health becomes a priority. Seniors often realize the value of taking care of themselves and setting boundaries.\n\n### 9. **Choices Define Your Path**\n   - Decisions about majors, internships, and extracurriculars shape your future. Seniors often reflect on whether they made the right choices and what they\u2019ve learned from them.\n\n### 10. **Friendships Will Change**\n   - As people move on to different paths, seniors realize that maintaining friendships post-college requires effort and intention.\n\n### 11. **You\u2019re More Capable Than You Think**\n   - By senior year, many students have overcome challenges and accomplished goals they once thought were impossible. This builds confidence in their abilities.\n\n### 12. **The Value of Independent Thinking**\n   - College teaches you to think critically and form your own opinions. Seniors often realize the importance of staying curious and open-minded.\n\n### 13. **Learning Continues Beyond the Classroom**\n   - Seniors recognize that education doesn\u2019t stop at graduation. Lifelong learning is key to personal and professional growth.\n\n### 14. **You\u2019ll Make Mistakes, and That\u2019s Okay**\n   - By senior year, most students have learned to accept failures as part of the learning process and realize they can bounce back.\n\n### 15. **Gratitude for the Experience**\n   - Despite the challenges, many seniors feel grateful for the opportunities, friendships, and lessons college has provided.\n\nSenior year is a time of introspection and preparation, filled with both nostalgia for the past and excitement for the future. It\u2019s a year to savor the present while planning for what\u2019s next.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
